      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DODGY DANNY (1) charged out of the boxes with a slick early split and went straight to the front, giving a huge sight but headed late when a 0.8 lengths second (27.86) over 488m at this track. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Leading chance again. CANYA CELESTE (2) collided with another runner and finished a well held 14 lengths seventh (35.60) last time in a Grade 5 at Cannington over 601m. Expected to feature on best. CYPHER MONELLI (3) filled the minor placings again last time when third (28.12) at this track, making it three straight minors on end. Looks well placed here and has the ability. Go well. DEAR ELIZA (7) is a last start winner worth following up.",
